<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Anne Hathaway has been getting in some quality family time with her husband and sons during quarantine.</p>

<p>But the Academy Award winner is getting back to her daily routine, as the film industry bounces back from COVID-19.</p>

<p>She served kisses Saturday in a cute face mask that featured red lips, as she stepped out of a New York City hair salon in a casual chic plaid blazer look.</p>

<p>Kiss kiss: Anne Hathaway served kisses Saturday in a cute face mask that featured red lips, as she stepped out of a New York City hair salon in a casual chic plaid blazer look</p>

<p>The 37-year-old wore the red and gray coat open, over a white t-shirt, which was tucked into some slim straight-leg high-waisted jeans.</p>

<p>She finished the look with some diamond stud earrings, a gold bangle, a light grey braided belt and a pair of nude leather pointed booties.</p>

<p>Hathaway had her hands full, as she carried a red leather crossbody bag and a blue leather tote bag. </p>

<p>She previously took to Instagram with a tribute to Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, who died Friday at 87 years old.</p>

<p>Casual chic: The 37-year-old wore the red and gray coat open, over a white t-shirt, which was tucked into some slim straight-leg high-waisted jeans</p>

<p>Accessorizing: She finished the look with some diamond stud earrings, a gold bangle, a light grey braided belt and a pair of nude leather pointed booties</p>

<p>RIP: She previously took to Instagram with a tribute to Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, who died Friday at 87 years old</p>

<p>The Devil Wears Prada actress wrote: 'God bless you and keep you, Ruth. We can never thank you enough. Rest in power, #RBG.'</p>

<p>Hathaway is currently in talks to star in a pandemic-themed romantic comedy/heist flick entitled Lockdown.</p>

<p>Directed by Doug Liman, the movie is set against the COVID-19 pandemic, and it's expected to begin filming in London by end of September. </p>

<p>Many have taken to social media to express their disapproval of the film's timing, given the current economic and health crises caused by the coronavirus.</p>

<p>Hathaway can next be seen as the Grand High Witch in Robert Zemeckis' adaptation of Roald Dahl's 1983 literary classic The Witches, which is scheduled to premiere in 2021.</p>

